<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Application Performance Monitoring (APM) on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/</link><description>Recent content in Application Performance Monitoring (APM) on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>pt-BR</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>1. APM Service Map</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/1-apm-service-map/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/1-apm-service-map/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;O APM Service Map exibe as dependências e conexões entre seus serviços instrumentados e inferidos em APM. O mapa é gerado dinamicamente com base nas suas seleções de intervalo de tempo, ambiente, transação de negócio, serviço e filtros de tags.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quando clicamos no link de APM no waterfall de RUM, filtros foram adicionados automaticamente à visualização do service map para mostrar os serviços envolvidos naquela &lt;strong&gt;Transaction&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;code&gt;frontend:/cart/checkout&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Você pode ver os serviços envolvidos no workflow no &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt;. No painel lateral, são exibidos gráficos para a transação selecionada. Quando você seleciona um serviço no &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt;, os gráficos no painel lateral são atualizados para mostrar métricas do serviço selecionado.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. APM Service View</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/2-apm-service-view/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/2-apm-service-view/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Service View&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;Como responsável por um serviço, você pode usar a service view no Splunk APM para obter uma visão completa da saúde do seu serviço em um único painel. A service view inclui um indicador em nível de serviço (SLI) para disponibilidade, dependências, métricas de request, error e duration (RED), métricas de runtime, métricas de infraestrutura, Tag Spotlight, endpoints e logs para um serviço selecionado. Você também pode navegar rapidamente para code profiling e memory profiling do seu serviço a partir da service view.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Ampliar o período para expor erros&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confira a caixa &lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;. Você pode ver que os dashboards mostram apenas dados relevantes ao tempo que o trace de APM selecionado anteriormente levou para concluir (observe que os gráficos são estáticos).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Na caixa &lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;, altere o período para &lt;strong&gt;-1h&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-service-dashboard.png" alt="Service Dashboard" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. APM Tag Spotlight</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/3-apm-tag-spotlight/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/3-apm-tag-spotlight/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Encontrar a versão ruim no Tag Spotlight&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ao entrar em &lt;strong&gt;Tag Spotlight&lt;/strong&gt;, garanta que o toggle &lt;strong&gt;Show tags with no values&lt;/strong&gt; esteja desligado.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-tag-spotlight.png" alt="APM Tag Spotlight" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Esta visualização exibe uma série de cards, cada um representando uma tag indexada (como Endpoint, Environment, Version ou tags customizadas como tenant.level). Dentro de cada card, você vê a distribuição dos valores da tag junto com métricas principais, incluindo contagem de requisições, contagem de erros, erros de causa raiz e percentis de latência (P50, P90, P99).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;Pergunta&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;Resposta&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qual card expõe a tag que identifica qual é o problema?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;O card &lt;em&gt;version&lt;/em&gt;. O número de requisições contra &lt;code&gt;v350.10&lt;/code&gt; corresponde ao número de erros, ou seja, 100%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agora que identificamos a tag que indica o problema, vamos ver se conseguimos encontrar mais informações sobre o erro.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no link &lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt; acima de &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; no topo da página para voltar para o &lt;strong&gt;APM Overview&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Em &lt;strong&gt;APM Overview&lt;/strong&gt;, clique em &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt; no painel à direita.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. APM Service Breakdown</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/4-apm-service-breakdown/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/4-apm-service-breakdown/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Detalhar o serviço por versão&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selecione o &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; no Service Map.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No painel à direita, clique em &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: var(--color-ink-muted)"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Breakdown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selecione &lt;code&gt;version&lt;/code&gt; na lista.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;Pergunta&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;Resposta&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;O que você pode concluir a partir do que está vendo?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Não há erros para &lt;code&gt;v350.9&lt;/code&gt;, mas &lt;code&gt;v350.10&lt;/code&gt; claramente tem um problema.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-service-breakdown.png" alt="APM Service Breakdown" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Span Tags&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. APM Trace Analyzer</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/5-apm-trace-analyzer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/5-apm-trace-analyzer/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Chegamos ao &lt;strong&gt;Trace Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O &lt;strong&gt;Trace Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt; é uma ferramenta poderosa do Splunk APM para explorar e analisar traces distribuídos em escala. Como o Splunk APM captura todos os traces com fidelidade completa (NoSample), você tem visibilidade total de todas as transações que passam pelos seus serviços.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O Trace Analyzer permite:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pesquisar com tags de alta cardinalidade&lt;/strong&gt;: filtre traces usando qualquer span tag indexada, como IDs de cliente, IDs de pedido ou atributos customizados de negócio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visualizar padrões de trace&lt;/strong&gt;: veja contagens de traces e erros ao longo do tempo para identificar tendências e anomalias.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analisar a distribuição de latência&lt;/strong&gt;: use a visualização de heatmap para entender padrões de duração dos traces e localizar outliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aprofundar em traces específicos&lt;/strong&gt;: encontre rapidamente o trace exato de que você precisa, seja para investigar uma reclamação de cliente ou depurar uma transação específica.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isso torna o Trace Analyzer ideal para investigar problemas desconhecidos, pesquisar transações específicas e fazer análise de causa raiz quando você precisa encontrar uma agulha no palheiro.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>6. APM Waterfall</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/6-apm-waterfall/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/6-apm-waterfall/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A visualização &lt;strong&gt;Trace Waterfall&lt;/strong&gt; mostra todos os spans de um trace como uma linha do tempo hierárquica. Cada span aparece como uma barra horizontal, em que o comprimento da barra representa sua duração e sua posição mostra quando ele ocorreu em relação aos outros spans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Um trace é uma coleção de spans que compartilham o mesmo trace ID, representando uma transação única processada pela sua aplicação e pelos serviços que a compõem.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>7. APM para Logs</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/7-apm-to-logs/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/7-apm-to-logs/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Ir de APM para Related Logs&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agora que identificamos a versão do &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; que está causando o problema, vamos ver se conseguimos encontrar mais informações sobre o erro. É aqui que entram os &lt;strong&gt;Related Logs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Related Content depende de metadados específicos que permitem que APM, Infrastructure Monitoring e Log Observer passem filtros entre áreas do Observability Cloud. Para que logs relacionados funcionem, você precisa ter os seguintes metadados nos seus logs:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>